<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Education_and_scholarly_res=
earch">Education and scholarly research</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection">=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAnalytic_hierarchy_process&amp;action=3Dedit&am=
p;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Education and scholarly research"><sp=
an>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></d=
iv>
<p>Though using the analytic hierarchy process requires no specialized acad=
emic training, it is considered an important subject in many institutions o=
f higher learning, including schools of engineering<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_hiera=
rchy_process#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Business_school" title=3D"Business school">graduate schools of bus=
iness</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_hierarchy_process#cite_note-18"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It=
 is a particularly important subject in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Quality_(business)" title=3D"Quality (business)">quality</a> fiel=
d, and is taught in many specialized courses including <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Sigma" title=3D"Six Sigma">Six Sigma</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lean_Six_Sigma" title=3D"Lean Six Sigma">=
Lean Six Sigma</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quality_fu=
nction_deployment" title=3D"Quality function deployment">QFD</a>.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Analytic_hierarchy_process#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-20"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_hier=
archy_process#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-21" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_hierarchy_process=
#cite_note-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>21<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Symposium=
_on_the_Analytic_Hierarchy_Process" title=3D"International Symposium on the=
 Analytic Hierarchy Process">International Symposium on the Analytic Hierar=
chy Process</a> (ISAHP) holds biennial meetings of academics and practition=
ers interested in the field. A wide range of topics is covered. Those in 20=
05 ranged from "Establishing Payment Standards for Surgical Specialists", t=
o "Strategic Technology Roadmapping", to "Infrastructure Reconstruction in =
Devastated Countries".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-22" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_hierarchy_process#cite_note-22">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup>
At the 2007 meeting in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valpara%C3%=
ADso,_Chile" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Valpara=C3=ADso, Chile">Valpara=
=C3=ADso, Chile</a>,  90 papers were presented from 19 countries, including=
 the US, Germany, Japan, Chile, Malaysia, and Nepal.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ISA=
HP2007_23-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A=
nalytic_hierarchy_process#cite_note-ISAHP2007-23"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A similar num=
ber of papers were presented at the 2009 symposium in <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pittsburgh,_Pennsylvania" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania">Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania</a>, when 28 countri=
es were represented.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ISAHP2009_24-0" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_hierarchy_process#cite_n=
ote-ISAHP2009-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Subjects of the papers included <i>Economic S=
